			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Led by a seasoned team of entrepreneurs, marketers, technologists and quants from such companies as Google, DoubleClick, CitiGroup and the NSA, RightAction is the leading provider of digital media trading technology and services.&nbsp; At the core of their service is an RTB ad-serving platform which offers human-focused analytical capabilities to optimize ROI and ROS goals.</p>
<p>
<br />
RightAction is currently seeking a highly qualified and experienced Sales Director with exceptional sales, communication, organization, and analytical skills. In this critical role, the Sales Director will be responsible for the identification, targeting, and execution of online media and technology companies. This will consist mainly of client-facing information discovery, proposal development, and translation of learnings into strategic and tactical recommendations, contract execution, and identification of upsell opportunities.</p>
<p>
<u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work to develop strategic plan to achieve revenue goals; hit or exceed these revenue goals</li>
<li>
Cultivate relationships with publishers, ad networks, trading desks and holding companies with the goal of attracting them to subscribe to the RightAction platform.</li>
<li>
Develop and expand advertiser and agency partnerships with detailed attention to client needs, development of case studies for purpose of broadcasting agency-client wins and for up-selling within agency</li>
<li>
Develop and maintain strong active relationships with key client stakeholders at both senior and mid-management levels</li>
<li>
Develop an understanding of and effectively communicate RightAction&rsquo;s value proposition, technology, processes, partnerships as it relates to growth of current and prospective client accounts</li>
<li>
Develop in-depth knowledge of the industry and of the real time biddable marketplace</li>
<li>
Other responsibilities, as may be required, such as: conference attendance, industry event attendance, and other substantive activities as we may decide</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
5-8 years of experience working in the Digital Ad space in a sales capacity</li>
<li>
Must have an understanding of agency, advertiser, data and vendor landscapes and trends and can answer questions like: Who are the major players, how do they buy, from whom; how do they shift budgets and strategic direction?</li>
<li>
Track record of exceeding goals and targets</li>
<li>
Self motivated, driven</li>
<li>
Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written</li>
<li>
Excellent presentation skills</li>
<li>
Desire to work among innovators in a collaborative environment</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
