			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<u><strong>Overview:</strong></u></p>
<p>
RightAction is an innovative online advertisement and technology company. We allow companies to buy online advertising media more efficiently and effectively by delivering simple solutions through complex data analysis. We are one of the fastest growing start-ups in Philadelphia, and are located in the Cira Centre next to 30th Street Station, just a short walk from the heart of Center City.</p>
<p>
We are currently looking to hire an experienced<strong> Software Engineer</strong> to assist with the development of our client web application.&nbsp; In this role, you will work directly with the RightAction CEO to understand client needs and build out the application.&nbsp; You will be a member of the core development team and collaborate with that team to divide features into workable sets. In addition to the core dev team, you may also need to collaborate with our statistician to assist in data retrieval, bring up new nodes, and maintain a growing, scalable platform.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
As you grow in this role, the expectation is that you would be able to learn the architecture of the entire system and be able to contribute to all aspects of development.&nbsp; This will include working with core Java, Amazon Web Services (EC2, S3, SQS, DynamoDB), Hadoop, messaging through ZeroMQ, provisioning through Chef, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
As an integral part of the Development Team, you will be expected to keep up with industry trends and be ready to learn and work with new technologies.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong><u>Responsibilities:</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop new product features and advance the design of existing code for client web application.</li>
<li>
Development work includes working with Java,&nbsp;Javascript based on DocumentCloud&rsquo;s Backbone.js MVC framework, and Ruby in the backend Rails application.</li>
<li>
Participate in sprint planning.</li>
<li>
React to possible production issues.</li>
<li>
Maintain open and consistent lines of communication with team members and the CEO.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<u><strong>Qualifications/Experience:</strong></u></p>
<p>
<strong><em>Required</em></strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Object oriented experience in Java, C#, or Python.</li>
<li>
Experience with Amazon Web Services (DynamoDB, EMR, SQS)</li>
<li>
Familiarity with REST principals; strong debugging skills; test driven development.</li>
<li>
Experience w/ system performance evaluation, monitoring, and benchmarking skills</li>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s degree</li>
<li>
Several years professional experience, or the ability to learn rapidly. (This is not an entry-level job.)</li>
<li>
Ability to clearly communicate technical concepts to a non-technical audience.</li>
<li>
Excellent organizational and interpersonal communication skills.</li>
<li>
Motivated self-starter.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<em><strong>Desired</strong></em>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Technical: Backbone.js, Twitter Bootstrap, Rails, Gems.</li>
<li>
Big Data experience using Hadoop</li>
<li>
Distributed sytstem architecture and design experience (SOA or SaaS)</li>
<li>
Proficiency with a Unix command line.</li>
<li>
Familiarity with NoSQL, Dependency Injection, Amazon Web Services (EC2, SQS, S3).</li>
<li>
Project configuration and deployment (e.g. Chef, Capistrano, Nginx).</li>
<li>
Experience with all stages of development from start to finish</li>
</ul>
<p>
